OperatorAdded(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `lister` adds `operator` to their pre-approve list.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.
params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                  collectors subscribed to `lister`.
params.startTime: The Unix timestamp when the `operator` can begin to manage                  NFTs on on behalf of collectors subscribed to `lister`.

OperatorRemoved(address,address).details: Emitted when `lister` removes `operator` from their pre-approve list. The `operator` will be immediately removed from the list.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.
params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                  collectors subscribed to `lister`.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.
params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.
params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

addOperator(address).details: Adds the `operator` to the pre-approve list maintained by the caller (lister).

params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                 collectors subscribed to the caller.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.
params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

isPreApproved(address,address,address).details: Returns whether the `operator` can manage NFTs on the behalf      of `collector` if `collector` is subscribed to `lister`.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.
params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.
params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                  collectors subscribed to `lister`.

operatorAt(address,uint256).details: Returns the operator at `index` of the pre-approve list by `lister`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.
params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                 collectors subscribed to `lister`.

operators(address).details: Returns the list of operators in the pre-approve list by `lister`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

removeOperator(address).details: Removes the `operator` from the pre-approve list maintained by the caller (lister).

params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                 collectors subscribed to the caller.

startTime(address,address).details: Returns the Unix timestamp when `operator` is able to start managing      the NFTs of collectors subscribed to `lister`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.
params.operator: The account that can manage NFTs on behalf of                 collectors subscribed to `lister`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

subscriptionAt(address,uint256).details: Returns the `lister` which `collector` is subscribed to at `index`.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.
params.index: The index of the enumerable set.

returns.lister: The mainter of the pre-approve list.

subscriptions(address).details: Returns an array of all the listers which `collector` is subscribed to.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.

totalOperators(address).details: Returns the list of operators in the pre-approve list by `lister`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

returns.total: The length of the list of operators.

totalSubscriptions(address).details: Returns the total number of listers `collector` is subscribed to.

params.collector: The NFT collector using the registry.

returns.total: The length of the list of listers subscribed by `collector`.

params.lister: The maintainer of the pre-approve list.

START_DELAY.details: The amount of time before a newly added `operator` becomes effective.

_startTimes.details: For extra efficiency, we use our own custom mapping for the mapping of (`lister`, `operator`) => `startTime`. If `startTime` is zero, it is disabled. Note: It is not possible for any added `operator` to have a `startTime` of zero, since we are already past the Unix epoch.

userdoc.notice: A on-chain registry where listers can create lists         of pre-approved operators, which NFT collectors can subscribe to.         When a collector is subscribed to a list by a lister,         they can use pre-approved operators to manage their NFTs         if the NFT contracts consult this registry on whether the operator         is in the pre-approved list by lister.         For safety, newly added operators will need to wait some time         before they take effect.
